UID:QmFllNtyFQ03Cvu_KO4DF
SUMMARY:Improvised Musical Style and Lyrics Class with Ron Hippe
DTSTAMP:20260410T044143Z
DTSTART:20260422T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Find Your Voice\\\, Build Your Confidence\\\, and Create Songs 
	on the Spot! \\n\\n\\n\\n\\nNow at Unexpected Productions’ new Issaquah lo
	cation\\\, unlock your creativity in a supportive\\\, playful\\\, and joy-
	filled class designed for anyone who’s ever hummed in the car\\\, belted i
	n the shower\\\, or wondered\\\, “How do musical improvisers make that mag
	ic happen?” \\nWhether you’re a seasoned improviser or stepping into music
	al improv for the first time\\\, this course welcomes you with open arms—n
	o prior singing experience required. \\nWhat You’ll Learn\\nThis intensive
	\\\, dynamic class explores the foundational skills of musical improvisati
	on through hands-on practice and group collaboration. You’ll learn how to:
	 \\n\\nCreate songs and stories in the moment\\nUnderstand classic song fo
	rms and how they apply to improv\\nStrengthen your sense of timing\\\, rhy
	thm\\\, and rhyme\\nTurn simple prompts into memorable choruses\\nBuild ly
	rics that feel poetic\\\, emotional\\\, or downright hilarious\\nJump conf
	idently between styles—from Broadway to jazz\\\, pop to chants\\n\\nIt’s f
	un\\\, supportive\\\, and incredibly energizing. You’ll be surprised at wh
	at you can create with your classmates—often within minutes. Unexpected Pr
	oductions Improv School is thrilled to bring our newest Eastside improv cl
	asses to Issaquah\\\, serving the communities of the Sammamish Plateau\\\,
	 East Renton\\\, Bellevue\\\, Snoqualmie Valley\\\, North Bend and beyond.
	 \\nClass Details\\nDates: Four (4) Wednesdays \\nTime: 7:00pm–9:00pm \\nL
	ocation: Unexpected Productions – Issaquah \\n1315 NW Mall Street\\\, Suit
	e 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA 98027 (next to the Gaslamp Bar and Grill) \\nMaxim
	um Students: 16 \\nCost: $270 \\nInstructor: Ron Hippe \\nRon Hippe joined
	 Unexpected Productions in 1990 and has performed globally—from San Franci
	sco to London and Vienna. He has appeared on Broadway in the Pulitzer Priz
	e-winning The Kentucky Cycle and worked with Seattle Rep\\\, ACT\\\, and I
	ntiman. Ron is also a veteran voice-over artist\\\, actor\\\, musician\\\,
	 and singer-songwriter. His teaching style is upbeat\\\, encouraging\\\, a
	nd rooted in decades of professional experience. \\nCancellation Policy:\\
	nWe are unable to offer refunds.\n\nhttps://www.unexpectedproductions.org/
	event/improvised-musical-style-and-lyrics-class-with-ron-hippe/\n\nFrom Un
	expected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/improvised-musical-style-an
	d-lyrics-class-with-ron-hippe/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions Improv School ISSAQUAH/EASTSIDE\\\, 1315 NW
	 Mall Street\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA\\\, 98108\\\, United States
